task.summary: Default task
Removed recursive sub-containers and updated SDP spec. version system usage to reflect changes in the spec.
Forgot to remove the recursive tag in the sub-container header + reflected changes in SDPStreambuf + incremented minor of spec.
Removed unused files in the tools dir.
Used a cleaner way to reset the structs.
Fixed some odd spacing.
Added compressed and encrypted tag to sub-container type in the header. + reflected changes in SDPStreamBuf.
Forgot to add the typedefs to the CMakeLists...
getSDPSubContainerHeader -> getSDPSubContainerInfo
Fixed more odd spacing.
Made some eos detection within the header checking.
Fixed some slight spacing derpage.
Fixed an error check. + cleaned up a struct resetting I forgot.
Finished implementing openSDP().
Implemented an openSDP to directly open files.
Fixed some include derpage.
Implemented setSubContainer().
Removed useless includes.
Switched SDPEncryptionAlgorithmBase to use uint style variables.
Removed isSeekingSupported in SDPEncryptionAlgorithmBase, seeking is now obligatory to all encryption algorithms.
Added getting/setting of the encryption algorithm ID in SDPEncryptionAlgorithmBase.
Removed checking of bounds for the encryption/compression algorithm ID so that user defined algorithms/IDs don't invalidate the sub-container's header.
Missed some types in the uint style conversion.
Removed onRewind in SDPEncryptionAlgorithmBase, now useless.
Removed decrypt/encryptStream in SDPEncryptionAlgorithmBase, deemed useless. + forgot more types to change into uint style...
Converted tabs to spaces in SDPEncryptionAlgorithmBase.
Changed data types to uint style in SDPCompressionAlgorithmBase.
Re-added encrypt/decryptStream... They're still useful... + some spacing underpage.
SDPCompressionOptions -> SDPCompressionAlgorithmInfoStruct.
Made typed uint style for SDPCompressionStreamBuf.
Added a tag in the compressed data block to tell if compression was skipped in the case that the block was incompressible.
Added capability to compression algorithms to be aware of the position in the stream they're working on.
Removed support for byte per byte compression, byte in byte out, no compression can happen on a single byte.
Added buffer size checking for prefered buffer size with overhead.
Forgot a couple things when removing byte per byte compression.
Gave compression algorithm ability to know the size of the uncompressed chunk.
Implemented a read function to read the compressed data chunk in accordance to the new spec.
Implemented a write function to write the compressed data chunk in accordance to the new spec.
Compression streambuf now uses the read/write function that conforms to the new spec.
Added DEFLATE to the default compression algorithms and changed compress/decompress -> compressBuffer/decompressBuffer to avoid function name collisions...
Re-added some testing stuff.
Added buffer size checking for the one with overhead in the encryption algorithm base.
Implemented read/write encrypted data chunk functions for SDPCryptStreamBuf.
Made SDPCryptStreamBuf use the read/write functions recently added + compiler error fixes.
Fixed some compiler errors on TEST build.
Fixed the SIGSEGV when reading past the last compressed chunk
Removed some test variables.
Moved test. + Added get encryption info function to SDPCryotStreamBuf.
Implemented XSalsa20 Algorithm + changed encrypt/decrypt -> encryptBuffer/decryptBuffer to avoid possible function name collisions.
Forgot license info...
